<h2>What we <em>can</em> and <em>can't</em> do</h2>
<p>We can do:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Provide guidance and technical support in program design and implementation &#8212; what to do and how to do it</li>
    <li>Assistance in securing program funding</li>
    <li>Assistance in identifying and engaging partners, in-country and globally</li>
    <li>Catalyze progress</li>
</ul>

<p>We can't do:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Run country programs</li>
    <li>Pay for programs</li>
    <li>Set country health and NCD prevention policy</li>
    <li>Sustain programs long-term</li>
</ul>

<h2>Team</h2>

<p>Our team of global health experts works with governments to help them implement evidence-based strategies that allow their citizens to lead the healthiest lives possible.</p>
<p>The New York City-based initiative is led by Dr. Tom Frieden, former director of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, and is housed within Vital Strategies.</p>

